Content:
renders it inflexible to asymmetrical and insurgent threats. The reliance on mass production and doctrinal rigidity might placate most of the galaxy, but it only takes one good spark—one outer rim planet that doesn’t fall in line, for the illusion of absolute control to falter.

As always in galactic history, strength breeds resistance. Whether the Empire will crush it under the weight of its might or collapse under its own ambition remains to be seen.

Until then, the Empire marches on—efficient, terrifying, and meticulously organized.
